-- Deploy Gated — human approval gate example.
-- Demonstrates the human cell type for interactive approval before deployment.
-- The pipeline: test -> human approval -> deploy.

## deploy-gated

  input param.branch : str required
  input param.env : str default("staging")

  -- Step 1: Run tests
  # run-tests : script
    ```bash
    echo "Running tests on {{param.branch}}..."
    echo "All 42 tests passed."
    ```
  #/

  -- Step 2: Analyze test results
  # analyze : llm
    - run-tests
    system>
      You summarize test results concisely.
    user>
      Test output:
      {{run-tests}}
      Summarize pass/fail counts and any notable failures.
    format> summary
      { passed: number, failed: number, notable: [str] }
  #/

  -- Step 3: Human approval gate
  # approve-deploy : human
    - analyze
    user>
      Environment: {{param.env}}
      Branch: {{param.branch}}
      Test summary: {{analyze}}
      Approve deployment?
    format> approval
      { approved: boolean, reason: str }
  #/

  -- Step 4: Deploy (only runs after human approves)
  # deploy : script
    - approve-deploy
    ```bash
    echo "Deploying {{param.branch}} to {{param.env}}..."
    echo "Deploy complete."
    ```
  #/

  -- Step 5: Notification
  # notify : text
    - deploy
    user>
      Deployment of {{param.branch}} to {{param.env}} complete.
      Approval: {{approve-deploy}}
      Deploy log: {{deploy}}
  #/

  run-tests -> analyze -> approve-deploy -> deploy -> notify

##/
